 <table-wrap-foot>
  <p>Beds correspond to annual average calculated from bed-days; peak in beds shown in parenthesis.</p>
  <p>Proj1=projections based solely on population growth.</p>
  <p>Proj2=Proj1 adjusted for public health intervention strategy.</p>
  <p>Population projections predicted a growth in lower respiratory tract infection (LRTI) bed-days of 5.5% among all children &lt;19 years of age and 16.3% among infants &lt;1 year of age by 2020 and 16.2% among all children &lt;19 years of age and 14.9% among infants &lt;1 year of age by 2030. A public health prevention strategy that reduces LRTI hospitalizations by 12.5% may counteract the effects of population growth.</p>
